init_text:
How Do You Think Technology Affects Dating?

Have you had any experience with dating? Have you ever used dating apps? If so, what has it been like for you? If not, why not?

How do you think technology — like apps, Netflix, social media and texting — affects dating and relationships? In your opinion, does it improve or worsen romantic interactions? How so?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The smartphone has given us the ability to replace great interpersonal connections with dehumanizing ones and can put a damper on relationships.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: However, it also allows us to connect with people we otherwise wouldn’t.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I think it is important to have multiple types of relationships and interactions to maintain proper self-care.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It is important not to allow all of our social connections to come from the digital realm.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Technology is a great tool and is more than just a distraction from our interpersonal relationships, but I think it should be used in a healthy moderation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Technology is great because it has enabled communication.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Before smartphones and texting I would speak to my partner only when we were together.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Now with texting and snap chat, I can communicate with him during when we are apart.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Technology can also be used to avoid issues or challenges with a relationship.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If we have a disagreement while we are with each other we can text or snapchat instead of arguing in person.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This way we can have a much less argument and deal with the issue in a civil manner.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Technology is a wonderful thing but can also be used destructively.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I think some of the best things are connecting with people.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I think there are also a lot of negatives with the communication aspects.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It can make relationships to different degrees superficial.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I don't feel "face to face" conversation is as important as it used to be.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Dating apps often make dating seem like a one-sided, automatic process.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It makes it easier to feel like dating is a game.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If someone doesn't respond within a day or two, you move on to the next person.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You don't get to know the person as well as you would in a normal situation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The amount of technology being used today hinders the normal dating process.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: With dating apps all that matters is you swiping left or right to get to the next person.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Technology certainly offers social benefits to those who lack friends and family.
